R.1 What It Is
	• Sometimes admins pre-create computer accounts in AD for new machines. They might set weak or default passwords.
R.2 Why It Matters
	• Attackers might guess or discover these passwords, effectively claiming the machine account and possibly pivoting or requesting tickets.
R.3 How to Exploit (Step-by-Step)
	1. Enumerate new or unused computer accounts.
	2. Check if they have a known or guessable password.
	3. Join the domain with that account if you can guess the password.
	4. Defend
		○ Use random strong passwords for pre-created accounts.
		○ Monitor unused computer accounts, remove or disable them if not used.
